# Bug Report

## Bug ID

BUG-001

---

## Title

User remains logged in after clicking **Logout** and using the browser Back button.

---

## Module

Authentication

---

## Severity

🔴 High

---

## Priority

High

---

## Environment

- Windows 11
- Google Chrome 139
- Application Version 2.1.0

---

## Preconditions

- User has successfully logged into the application.

---

## Steps to Reproduce

1. Log into the application.
2. Navigate to the dashboard.
3. Click **Logout**.
4. After reaching the login page, press the browser **Back** button.

---

## Expected Result

The user should remain logged out and be redirected to the login page if attempting to access protected pages.

---

## Actual Result

The dashboard becomes accessible again through browser history without requiring the user to authenticate.

---

## Impact

Unauthorized users with access to the same browser session may be able to view protected information.

---

## Frequency

Always

---

## Status

Open

---

## Suggested Investigation

Verify that authenticated pages are not cached after logout and ensure server-side session validation occurs whenever protected pages are accessed.

